Nov 13 2009 	A pleasant surprise	I had read many reviews about the Tez and its renovated rooms, but I was not totally convinced - however, as I was travelling alone, the price was right and I only needed a place to crash after gambling the farm away and drinking myself to oblivion I figured that I would give the El Cortez a try.My 2 queen beds tower room was totally renovated and a lot better than the rooms I've had recently at Imperial Palace, Boulder Station, Texas Station and Fiesta Rancho - not to mention dives like Plaza, Vegas Club and Terribles. The only negative point was the old television set - but who goes to Las Vegas to watch television?The food options are quite limited: an &quot;upscale&quot; steakhouse, a coffee shop and a sub shop, but at par with what you would encounter in any downtown casino. The gambling is great - good VP, loose slots and THE BEST single deck blackjack in town (stil paying 3:2). They have upgraded the rooms and the casino - now they need to upgrade their patronage, and I am afraid it will take a while until the people that used to favor the property when it was the third worst hotel-casino in town (after the Western and the Gold Spike) go looking for greener pastures.If you are looking for good odds instead of volcanos, pirate battles and water shows and if a swiming pool is not high on your priorities list, I am sure you will love the El Cortez.	
Nov 12 2009 	great for the price	I am a frequent visitor to Vegas and have always stayed on the Strip, this was my first time staying in the Freemont area. I thought I would try it for the nostalgia aspect. This is one of the true old Vegas hotels with lots of history. The hotel itself was clean, beds were good and AC worked. Security was in the parking lots to protect your cars. If you are in Vegas to gamble or sight see the El is a great place to stay. This is not one of the new hotels on the Strip so do not expect the same amenities. If that is the experience you are seeking then spend the additional funds and stay on the Strip. The staff at the El are friendly, helpful and quick to react to requests. The Freemont nightlife is well worth seeing and experiencing. For an inexpensive place to stay in Vegas I would highly recommend the El Cortez..	
