et minded people. I'm to understand the more expensive rooms are much larger and have nicer views. Perhaps on our next trip I will upgrade. If you have Strip related business, you must allow for travel time. You can bypass the traffic/crowds on the Strip/Bus and take the Public City Bus that almost runs a loop around the strip. If you are driving, Maryland Ave. runs parallel about 5 blocks to the East of the Strip.Vegas is a fun place to visit for an interesting vacation.Due to the 3 hour time change, the travel delay, jet lag, the bright lights, noises, smells of the city, adult oriented themes, wedding chapels on almost every corner and general humanity it was a Surreal Experience. One that I hope to experience again soon!!!	
