Apr 20 2006	The Good and The Bad - With Photos	THE FACTS: Stayed weekday,Tower, corner room (rooms in the corner with numbers ending in 14 or 15 are slightly larger). THE GOOD: 1) Cheap place to stay. $40. 2) Biggest standard room I've stayed in. Corner rooms only. 3) Clean for an older room. 4) Parking lot well lit. 5) Air conditioning worked great.THE BAD: 1) The area surrounding is suspect. Not recommended for kids/elderly. 2) Heard alot of &quot;security to...&quot; in casino from workers with walkie talkies. 3) Parking is free for everyone, so can be hard to find at night. Upper levels were closed that night for some reason. 4) Bathrooms are small, but typical of older hotels. 5) Hot water more like luke warm in the late morning. Other times fine.CONCLUSION: My wife and I would stay here again if looking for a cheap place at the last minute. We thought the rooms were very spacious and generally clean, although we can't attest to the carpet since we travel with slippers. We stayed at the Las Vegas Club on Fremont the night before and The California the night after and El Cortez was much better than Vegas Club, but not as nice as California (both reviewed). We didn't try the restaurants at the El. Check out the photos, but excuse the mess!	
